image.altText: Rebel forces in Hama Syria

props.synopsis: Syrian rebels, in a televised address, say they have "freed" the country's capital, while President Bashar al-Assad has reportedly fled. Follow live.

title.children: Rebels bring down Assad regime in Syria as president reportedly flees

image.altText: President Bashar al-Assad and President Vladimir Putin shaking hands inside a Kremlin meeting room.

props.synopsis: Whatever the final outcome of the chaos in Syria, the past week has seen an extraordinary upheaval.

title.children: How the fall of Assad will change the Middle East

image.altText: people on platform with trains

props.synopsis: Two weeks of negotiations fail to secure a deal between the NSW government and rail unions, as transport officials head to the Federal Court to seek an injunction to stop further action.

title.children: Sydneysiders warned to expect major train delays after pay negotiations fail

image.altText: A crowd of people gathered at a vigil in a park during the daytime.

props.synopsis: Members of Melbourne's Jewish community have gathered for a vigil near the synagogue which was targeted by arsonists on Friday. The vigil comes ahead of a meeting of counter-terrorism police investigating the blaze.

props.synopsis: Ahead of law enforcement groups meeting tomorrow to discuss the arson attack at Ripponlea's Adass Israel synagogue, the prime minister says in his view it was an act of terrorism.

title.children: Albanese says Melbourne synagogue attack 'quite clearly' terrorism

image.altText: Pat Cummins high-fives Travis Head as he runs through in celebration

image.altText: Ellyse Perry of Australia celebrates a century, raising her bat and helmet to the crowd

props.synopsis: A record-breaking knock by Ellyse Perry and Georgia Voll's maiden international hundred have lifted Australia to a comprehensive 122-run victory over India in the second women's ODI in Brisbane.

title.children: Ellyse Perry breaks records as Australia secures series win with 122-run victory over India

image.altText: A man in a hoodie smiles in cctv footage

props.synopsis: American media are reporting that authorities know the identity of the suspect in the murder of UnitedHealth executive Brian Thompson, but they are not releasing the gunman's name yet.

title.children: New York mayor says 'net is tightening' on UnitedHealth CEO's suspected killer

image.altText: Peter Dutton wearing high vis and touring a brick factory

image.altText: A map of Australia.

image.altText: the new south wales premier chris minns stands at a lecturn at a press conference

image.altText: The Notre Dame at dusk, with a projection on the side lighting it up in neon green, pink and light blue.

image.altText: View over Bendigo, Victorial

image.altText: Man putting food waste into a stainless steel drum

image.altText: A man stands in a backyard with his arms crossed, looking into camera with a serious expression.

But after weeks of public hearings, the Opposition is making the most of the opportunity to spruik its plans.

image.altText: Spirit of Tasmania IV ship in port.

image.altText: Portrait of three men against a dark theatre background.

image.altText: A small white car surrounded by police tape.

image.altText: Sketch of school children at a large table. Four gathered at one end with a teacher and one alone at the other under a spotlight
